author: Tal_Golesworthy;
title: How I repaired my own heart

aws-transcripts.transcript: I'm a process engineer. I know all about boilers and incinerators and fabric filters and cyclones and things like that. But I also have Marfan syndrome. This is inherited disorder on DDE. In 1992 I participated in a genetic study and found to my horror, as you can see from the slide that my ascending aorta was not in the normal range the green line at the bottom. Everyone in here will be between three and 32236 centimetres already about 44 Onda. As you can see it, my auto dilated progressively, and I got closer and closer to the point where surgery was going to be necessary. The surgery on author was pretty gruesome.
